      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRINCESS MILA (8) was well supported last time and rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but had to settle for the minor money, finishing a nose second (22.64) over 400m at this track. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. One of the leading chances. BENNY THE BULL (3) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 22.64 beating PRINCESS MILA. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Significant danger. MR. TAYLOR (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the money last time though when third (22.86) at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Will give a great sight again. IMPRESS ROCKS (7) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
